PN,41201
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F412A1775736665
OL,3,CShipwreck with explosives aboard set
OL,4,Cto have masts reduced in #9.5 million
OL,5,Cdeal
OL,7,FA World War Two shipwreck with
OL,8,Fexplosives aboard is set to have its
OL,9,Fmasts reduced in size as part of a
OL,10,F#9.5 million deal.
OL,12,FThe Department for Transport (DfT)
OL,13,Fcould sign a contract as soon as
OL,14,FThursday to cut and remove the SS
OL,15,FRichard Montgomery's masts.
OL,17,FThe US Liberty ship, built in 1943,
OL,18,Fran aground in the Thames Estuary in
OL,19,FAugust 1944, between the Kent and
OL,20,FEssex coasts.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/6
